during the hazard review that the North Columbus River Pump Station has the necessary equipment and the operating and training procedures required for the safe operation of the chlorination system.  During the most recent hazard review, the hazard review team made the following recommendations for improving the safe operating procedures and for minimizing the likelihood of an offsite release from the chlorination system:
1. Require personnel entering the chlorine building to carry a mouth-bit escape respirator and chemical safety goggles while in the building;
2. Require operators to complete crane operator training before transferring one-ton containers using the hoist system;
3. Require hoist inspections that follow ANSI and OSHA guidelines;
4. Require operators and maintenance employees to complete the Chlorine Institute Training Program, "Safe Handling of Chlorine"; and
5. Require a hot work permit system for any cutting and welding inside the chlorine building.
